//gray-walb-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/https%3A%2F%2Fdo0bihdskp9dy.cloudfront.net%2F12-02-2025%2Ft_877716b9f977412ea948c884b4ada0a7_name_file_1280x720_2000_v3_1_.jpg?auth=f6adc4386785fb871b5ef09bfb421e75b174b16b2355a8bd0f7ed7b2e071efb4&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-walb-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/J5MU5XAQA5CT7OFTNMXUIJLXL4.jpg?auth=6d9df90d43ec5be0f63ab06e4d8752f26ac7ae1d3245a781286173f0f7c7ea07&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-walb-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/FUP2OJLVJZH4PDM6FCWYS4EMJA.jpg?auth=f51795f53a481151d0a3ecb5ed598f4d39ba431f611aef2752bff01e2d4e85dd&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-walb-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/EEF4FQCV5ZGKPONLYEJVNFVYZ4.jpg?auth=7c753147adea2f9532bb4fca95908787ff5789aacefa38bffb7d08aee51493f8&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-walb-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/XRBAYWJDBRHPVE7EXRWWWCPNUE.png?auth=5eaab92949a673e39476a1678cea2ea5abe28fedafd185f6f7b2de371ab66218&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "https://gray-walb-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/QEIHCTICG5F2PGFM5S5W3VY5CI.png?auth=15c5ef5b732f51c3ee2534fe0cdc43eb8e5956a35f31cac26ff677debbde91af&width=800&height=450&smart=true"], "publication-date": "2024-08-19", "text": "Moultrie, Ga. (WALB) - The city of Moultrie is gearing up to welcome home Moultrie native Carson Tyler with a parade.\n\nTyler is returning home today from Paris after competing in diving at the 2024 Summer Olympic Games.\n\nThe city of Moltrie posted on its Facebook page that a parade will be taking place tonight at 6 p.m.\n\nThey are asking residents to wear red, white, and blue to support Tyler.\n\nThe parade route is set to start at 1st Street SE in Moultrie, and head towards East Central Avenue where it will take a left, and end on South Main Street near Kirbo Law.\n\nAfter the parade wraps up, Tyler will go on a stage and the city will read a proclamation in his honor. He will then be presented a key to the city.\n\nOnce that wraps up, Tyler will be available to take pictures and sign autographs.\n\nTyler placed 4th in theMen’s 3-meter Diving event, and he also competed in the Men’s 10-meter diving event.\n\nHave a news tip or see an error that needs correction?Let us know.Please include the article’s headline in your message.\n\nTo stay up to date on all the latest news as it develops, follow WALB onFacebookandX (Twitter). For more South Georgia news, download the WALB News app from theApple StoreorGoogle Play.\n\nCopyright 2024 WALB. All rights reserved.", "title": "Moultrie to welcome home Carson Tyler from Olympics", "top-image": "https://gray-walb-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/XISFIHZU5RASFLEAZEGUR5HVE4.jpg?auth=8a6f8ab4be2e643c1d1ddbbaa3d01bae960261644cba4999c7129bddda6540b8&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "domain": "www.walb.com", "lang": "en", "author": "", "description": "The city of Moultrie is gearing up to welcome home Moultrie native Carson Tyler with a parade.", "keywords": "Moultrie,olympics,diving,carson tyler,team usa"}